# Response format — STARTER (replace with your own)

> This file is the single source of truth for how Claude formats every response
> in this project. It was seeded once by the domain Element's `bin/init`; the
> project owns it now — edit freely.
>
> Two companions (see `.claude/hooks/enforce-output-style.py` header):
> - `CLAUDE.md` points here, keeping the rule in context even when this style
>   isn't the active one.
> - `.claude/output-style.enforce.json` can hard-enforce the *checkable* parts
>   of this format, per session.

## Always

- **Lead with the answer.** The first line resolves the question; detail follows.
- **Stay structured.** Any response longer than a few sentences uses Markdown
  headings or bold section labels so it is scannable. *(This is the part the Stop
  hook checks by default.)*
- **Be direct.** No filler, no "I'd be happy to…", no hedging when something is
  clear. Say what's true; calibrate confidence explicitly when it isn't.
- **No emoji** unless explicitly asked.

## Checkable subset

A Stop hook can only verify *structurally checkable* rules, not prose style. The
default config (`.claude/output-style.enforce.example.json`) enforces exactly
one: responses past a length threshold must contain at least one Markdown heading
or bold label. Add or change checks in `.claude/output-style.enforce.json`; keep
the full, human-judged format here.
